A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Macon-Bibb County Industrial Authority (MBCIA) for its exceptional
2 contributions to economic development, investment attraction, and community partnerships
3 in Macon-Bibb County; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, the MBCIA has demonstrated outstanding leadership in fostering economic
5 growth, culminating in over $1 billion in investments in Macon-Bibb County during 2024;
6 and
7 WHEREAS, significant milestones achieved under the MBCIA's guidance include Irving
8 Tissue's announcement of a nearly $600 million expansion, adding at least 100 new jobs to
9 its Macon facility; First Quality Baby Products' announcement of a $418 million expansion,
10 further strengthening the local economy; YKK USA's celebration of 50 years of operation
11 in Macon, exemplifying long-term industrial commitment; and Embraer's reaffirmation of
12 its dedication to the region by signing a new 15-year lease, ensuring continued operations in
13 Macon; and
14 WHEREAS, the MBCIA has facilitated substantial contributions to local development and
15 education through the Payment in Lieu of Taxes (PILOT) Program, including a $1,941,643
16 check presented to the Bibb County School District, accepted by Superintendent Dan Sims,
