17 and a $1,929,580 check presented to Macon-Bibb County, accepted by Mayor Lester Miller;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, these strategic initiatives and partnerships have significantly enhanced the
20 economic landscape of Macon-Bibb County, creating employment opportunities, expanding
21 the tax base, and improving the quality of life for residents.
22 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
23 the members of this body commend the Macon-Bibb County Industrial Authority for its
24 exemplary efforts in driving economic development, attracting substantial investments, and
25 fostering collaborative relationships that benefit the entire community.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of this body recognize Board Chair Robby
27 Fountain, Executive Director Stephen Adams, and the leadership and staff of the
28 Macon-Bibb County Industrial Authority for their dedication, vision, and effective execution
29 of strategies that have positioned Macon-Bibb County as a premier destination for business
30 and industry.
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
32 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
33 Macon-Bibb County Industrial Authority.
